<chapter condition="TITLE=System Features - Entity;ACCESS=SY_ENTITY"
         role="TOPIC">
  <title role="">Entity Maintenance</title>

  <section role="ITEM">
    <title>Overview</title>

    <para role="TEXT">As an administrator at a client company, you use the
    <application moreinfo="none">Entity Maintenance</application> module to
    maintain entities within the company.</para>

    <para role="TEXT">This module has just one function on the System Features
    menu, called <emphasis role="bold">Entity Maintenance.</emphasis></para>
  </section>

  <section role="ITEM">
    <title>Entity Maintenance Form</title>

    <para>When you click this function, you are presented with a list of
    existing entities. You can search the list by entering search criteria in
    the <guilabel>Entity ID, Name, Status</guilabel> and
    <guilabel>Actor</guilabel> fields at the top of the page.<note>
        <para role="TEXT">Only the <guilabel>Entity ID </guilabel>and
        <guilabel>Name</guilabel> fields are available if maker-checker
        functionality is not enabled.</para>
      </note></para>

    <para role="TEXT">The list of the company's entities has the following
    columns:</para>

    <para role="TEXT"><informaltable>
        <tgroup cols="2">
          <colspec colname="c1" colwidth="2.0*"/>

          <colspec colname="c2" colwidth="8.0*"/>

          <thead>
            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">Field</para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">Description</para></entry>
            </row>
          </thead>

          <tbody>
            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"><guilabel moreinfo="none">
              Entity ID</guilabel> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">The defined name of the
              Entity.</para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <guilabel
              moreinfo="none">Name</guilabel> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">Name of the
              Entity.</para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para
              role="TEXT"><guilabel>Status</guilabel></para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">This indicates the status
              of the pending record set by the checker. </para><note>
                  <para role="TEXT">This column is only available if
                  maker-checker functionality is enabled.</para>
                </note></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"><guilabel>Maker User
              </guilabel></para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">Displays the user ID of
              the maker of the transaction.</para><note>
                  <para role="TEXT">This column is only available if
                  maker-checker functionality is enabled.</para>
                </note></entry>
            </row>
          </tbody>
        </tgroup>
      </informaltable></para>

    <para role="TEXT">You can modify an Entity by clicking the <guiicon
    moreinfo="none">Edit</guiicon> <inlinemediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata fileref="../images/icon_edit.gif" role="ICON_EDIT"
                     width="4mm"/>
        </imageobject>
      </inlinemediaobject> icon in the right-hand column, view it in
    non-editable mode by clicking the <guibutton>View</guibutton>
    <inlinemediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata fileref="../images/icon_popup.gif" role="ICON_POPUP"
                     width="4.5mm"/>
        </imageobject>
      </inlinemediaobject> icon, or delete it by clicking the <guibutton
    moreinfo="none">Delete</guibutton> <inlinemediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata fileref="../images/icon_trash.gif" role="ICON_TRASH"
                     width="4mm"/>
        </imageobject>
      </inlinemediaobject> icon. If maker-checker functionality is enabled,
    then the <guibutton moreinfo="none">Action</guibutton> <inlinemediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata fileref="../images/icon_makerchecker_action.gif"
                     role="ICON_TRASH" width="4mm"/>
        </imageobject>
      </inlinemediaobject> icon is displayed to the Checker if the entity
    creation is awaiting approval. And for entity creations awaiting approval,
    the <guibutton moreinfo="none">Cancel</guibutton> <inlinemediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata fileref="../images/icon_makerchecker_cancel.gif"
                     role="ICON_TRASH" width="4mm"/>
        </imageobject>
      </inlinemediaobject> icon is displayed to the Maker, which provides the
    Maker the option to cancel the entity creation by clicking this button
    before approval.</para>

    <note>
      <para role="TEXT">When you delete an Entity, its account and all its
      user accounts (including the administrator user) are deleted from the
      system. However, all transaction data is kept in the system for
      historical and inquiry purposes. They should be purged separately from
      the transaction functions.</para>
    </note>

    <para role="TEXT">Click the <guibutton moreinfo="none">Add a new
    entity</guibutton> button at the bottom of the list to add an
    account.</para>

    <para role="TEXT"><guiicon moreinfo="none">Edit</guiicon> and <guibutton
    moreinfo="none">Add</guibutton> display the same form, but in the case of
    <guibutton moreinfo="none">Edit</guibutton> it is preset with the existing
    details of the Customer Entity. After entering the details, click
    <emphasis role="bold">Submit</emphasis> at the bottom of the form.</para>

