    <section role="ITEM">
      <title>Customer Entity Form - System Settings</title>

      <para role="TEXT">This section contains the System settings for this
      entity: <informaltable>
          <tgroup cols="3">
            <colspec colname="c1" colwidth="3.3*"/>

            <colspec colname="c2" colwidth="1.2*"/>

            <colspec colname="c3" colwidth="5.3*"/>

            <thead>
              <row>
                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">Field</para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">Type</para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para
                role="TEXT">Description</para></entry>
              </row>
            </thead>

            <tbody>
              <row>
                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"><guilabel
                moreinfo="none">Authorise Own Transaction</guilabel>
                </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <inlinemediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                      <imagedata fileref="../images/char_check.gif"
                                 role="CHAR_CHECK" width="3mm"/>
                    </imageobject>
                  </inlinemediaobject> </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">You can select this
                option to enable users authorise their own transactions.
                </para><para role="TEXT">By default, this option is not
                selected, and any transaction will require authorisation by a
                user assigned with the appropriate role-permissions.
                </para></entry>
              </row>

              <row>
                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"><guilabel
                moreinfo="none">Bulk Authorise Limit at Payment</guilabel>
                </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <inlinemediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                      <imagedata fileref="../images/char_check.gif"
                                 role="CHAR_CHECK" width="3mm"/>
                    </imageobject>
                  </inlinemediaobject> </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">If you select this
                option, the system will check if the highest transaction
                amount of the bulk payment is within the set authorisation
                limit. If the amount exceeds the limit, the transaction will
                not be processed. </para><para role="TEXT">By default, this
                option is not selected, and the system will check whether the
                total amount of the bulk payments is within the set
                authorisation limit. If the total amount exceeds the limit,
                the transactions will not proceed. </para></entry>
              </row>

              <row>
                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"><guilabel
                moreinfo="none">Auto Forward Date</guilabel> </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <inlinemediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                      <imagedata fileref="../images/char_check.gif"
                                 role="CHAR_CHECK" width="3mm"/>
                    </imageobject>
                  </inlinemediaobject> </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">You can select this
                option to set auto forward of transaction processing dates.
                Transactions can be auto forwarded if the cut-off time is
                exceeded or if the transaction processing date is a holiday.
                </para><para role="TEXT">By default, this option is not
                selected. If it is in the not-selected state, you may have to
                amend the transaction processing date (if you created the
                transaction) or move the transaction to draft for amendment
                (if you are required to authorise the transaction).
                </para></entry>
              </row>

              <row>
                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <guilabel
                moreinfo="none">File Upload Settings</guilabel>
                </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"/></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">This subsection provides
                setting details for processing bulk upload of transactions
                from files. <note>
                    <para role="TEXT">The settings described here are
                    applicable only for the client's File Upload screen in
                    Cash Services. These settings are not applicable for file
                    upload features on other screens in the
                    application.</para>
                  </note></para></entry>
              </row>

              <row>
                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <guilabel
                moreinfo="none">Check File Hash Value</guilabel>
                </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <inlinemediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                      <imagedata fileref="../images/char_check.gif"
                                 role="CHAR_CHECK" width="3mm"/>
                    </imageobject>
                  </inlinemediaobject> </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">You can select this
                option if you want the system to check for hash values when
                files are uploaded. Any difference in the values in the file
                and the expected hash values will reject the file upload and
                generate an error log. </para><para role="TEXT">By default,
                this option is not selected.</para></entry>
              </row>

              <row>
                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <guilabel
                moreinfo="none">Check Duplicate Files (MD5)</guilabel>
                </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <inlinemediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                      <imagedata fileref="../images/char_check.gif"
                                 role="CHAR_CHECK" width="3mm"/>
                    </imageobject>
                  </inlinemediaobject> </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">You can select this
                option if you want the system to check and compare for MD5
                hash values between the file being uploaded and the file
                previously uploaded during the same calendar day (12AM to 12PM
                period). If the files share the same MD5 hash value, the
                system will reject the upload and display a message that the
                file cannot be uploaded. </para><para role="TEXT">By default,
                this option is not selected.</para></entry>
              </row>

              <row>
                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <guilabel
                moreinfo="none">Check Duplicate Customer Reference </guilabel>
                </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <inlinemediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                      <imagedata fileref="../images/char_check.gif"
                                 role="CHAR_CHECK" width="3mm"/>
                    </imageobject>
                  </inlinemediaobject> </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">You can select this
                option if you want the system to check bulk upload of
                transactions against the database for duplicate customer
                references. Any duplicate records found in the file will be
                treated according to whether the file type is amendable or
                non-amendable. </para><para role="TEXT">By default, this
                option is not selected, and in this state, the system will not
                check for any duplicate references and upload the
                transactions. </para></entry>
              </row>

              <row>
                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <guilabel
                moreinfo="none">File Upload Encryption Method</guilabel>
                </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <inlinemediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                      <imagedata fileref="../images/char_excla.gif"
                                 role="CHAR_EXCLA" width="2mm"/>
                    </imageobject>
                  </inlinemediaobject> </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">You can specify the
                encryption method to be used when uploading
                files.</para></entry>
              </row>

              <row>
                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <guilabel
                moreinfo="none">Non - Amendable File Types</guilabel>
                </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <inlinemediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                      <imagedata fileref="../images/char_radio.gif"
                                 role="CHAR_RADIO" width="3mm"/>
                    </imageobject>
                  </inlinemediaobject> </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">You can select the
                action to take for errors encountered in non-amendable files.
                The following options are available:</para><para
                role="TEXT"><programlisting format="linespecific">Reject whole file if any error
Process successful transactions and reject errors 
</programlisting></para></entry>
              </row>

              <row>
                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <guilabel
                moreinfo="none">Merge/de-merge/delete allowed</guilabel>
                </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <inlinemediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                      <imagedata fileref="../images/char_check.gif"
                                 role="CHAR_CHECK" width="3mm"/>
                    </imageobject>
                  </inlinemediaobject> </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">You can select this
                option if you want the system to merge, de-merge or delete
                transactions from bulk upload files. This applies only to
                non-amendable file types. </para><para role="TEXT">By default,
                this option is not selected. </para><note>
                    <para role="TEXT">Transactions from amendable file type
                    can be merged/de-merged/deleted.</para>
                  </note></entry>
              </row>

              <row>
                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <guilabel
                moreinfo="none">Amendable File Types</guilabel>
                </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT"> <inlinemediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                      <imagedata fileref="../images/char_radio.gif"
                                 role="CHAR_RADIO" width="3mm"/>
                    </imageobject>
                  </inlinemediaobject> </para></entry>

                <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">You can select the
                action to take for errors encountered in amendable files. You
                can use 'All bulks to draft if any error' to save as draft and
                repair the file. You can use 'Bulk successful and transaction
                with error separately' to process successful entries, and save
                any entries with errors as draft and repair the file.
                </para><para role="TEXT"><programlisting
                format="linespecific">All bulks to draft if any error
Bulk successful and transaction with error separately
</programlisting></para></entry>
              </row>
            </tbody>
          </tgroup>
        </informaltable></para>
    </section>

